content.title: 34 Sexually Graphic Movies With Lots of Nudity
content.content:
Nudity in movies has a long history. Right from 1915, when director Lois Weber chose to portray an actress naked for his film, to the most recent fandom fantasy premiere of ‘Game of Thrones,’ nudity has served its purpose in every aspect of filmmaking. With the advent of porn films, whatever little inhibitions filmmakers had in portraying nudity were let go. The thought process behind that was that people get to see nudity on-screen, so there should not be a big deal if they are shown in conventional movies. Other factors, such as prosthetics, technology, and better cameras, made filming and executing nude scenes easier.
     The list below primarily comprises Hollywood movies with the most nude scenes and lots of nudity. It does NOT cover documentaries or pornographic films. To the puerile souls that are smitten by the naked body of Kate Winslet in Titanic or nudity in general, here is a list of movies with lots of nudity. Please keep in mind that these movies have been ranked based on their nude scenes.
 
## 34. Cashback (2006)
 
 Sean Ellis’ ‘Cashback’ follows Ben Willes, whose insomnia, which has resulted from his recent breakup, has earned him more hours in a day. Moreover, his night clerk job at a supermarket makes him realize that he can stop time and alter the world around him without anyone knowing. This enables him to give shape to his talents as an artist, letting the movie address its coming-of-age theme. The women at the market become his subjects of beauty, and he starts undressing and drawing them. One of these days, he meets Sharon, for whom he develops feelings. Can she bring him out of his insomnia? ‘Cashback’ was meant to be an experimental short film but went on to become a feature film, which famed critic Roger Ebert addressed as “lightweight, as it should be.” The nude scenes are naturally when Ben undresses the women and sketches them, and there are lots of them. You can watch ‘Cashback’ [here](https://tubitv.com/movies/437589).
 
## 33. Tiger, Blood in the Mouth (2016)
 
 It is not a cinematic masterpiece, but the nudity factor pays off. Also, there are no tigers involved per se, not at least in their literal sense. An aging boxer, Ramon, who once had been a big shot, has lost all hope in his life and career. With his career on the sunset and his wife and kids demanding more attention from him, Deborah, a young, fervent female boxer at the onset of her career, enters. They both fall for each other (or rather lust for each other), and what follows is relentless fornication, nude scenes (which are a delight, yes?), and a lot of sexual encounters. Those who are looking for some boxing material should be prepared to be disappointed. If you’ve been longing to watch sex in a sports-related movie, this is the one for you. Stream it on Netflix right away.
 **Read More: [TV Shows With Most Nudity](https://thecinemaholic.com/tv-shows-with-nudity/)**
 
## 32. Boogie Nights (1997)
 
 Paul Thomas Anderson’s ‘Boogie Nights’ tracks the rise and fall of a young boy named Eddie Adams (Mark Wahlberg) as a pornstar during the Golden Age of Porn in the 1970s and its decline in the 1980s. With sex, drugs, and all other stuff symbolizing the so-called aspects of modernism at its center, the movie goes no-holds-barred in the depiction of the porn industry and its charming “excesses.” The movie is known for its graphic nudity. Actresses Julianne Moore and Heather Graham went nude for multiple scenes. Wahlberg, however, used a prosthetic penis for his nude shot, which he kept to himself after production wrapped. ‘Boogie Nights’ has stood the test of time and has earned the reputation of a cult classic.
 
## 31. Killing Me Softly (2002)
 
 A high-profile drama that relies more on sexual measures than the storyline, the film revolves around a woman who abandons her relationship with her boyfriend and ties herself to a mysterious mountain climber. Although it fails as a film progresses, ‘Killing Me Softly’ guarantees high thermal ambiance with Heather Graham’s lumped-up exposure alongside her co-star Joseph Fiennes. For the most part, ‘Killing Me Softly’ acts as a substitute thriller for ‘Unfaithful,’ which was released in the same year. You can watch the film [here](https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/detail/amzn1.dv.gti.86986637-213a-4207-86e7-a0ad0c78d4f8).
 
## 30. Wetlands (2013)
 
 Well, more than sexuality and eroticism, disgust is the first emotion that comes to mind when ‘Wetlands’ is concerned. To start with, Helen is a young lass who doesn’t believe in hygiene, prefers to sit naked with her genitals on all kinds of trash, and has no ambitions in life whatsoever. Recalling her sensual experiences from her childhood and with the apparent trauma of her separating parents, Helen prefers living an out-of-the-box, adventurous life for herself, including exploring all the options for her sexuality. She cuts herself while she’s been shaving her anus one fine day (yeah, you read that right!) and has to go to the ER, where she falls for Robin, a male nurse. With scenes depicting severed body parts, ample nudity, and disgusting sex scenes, but yet very minimal mainstream sex, ‘Wetlands’ is one of the weirdest movies on this list. You can watch it [here](https://www.amazon.com/Wetlands-English-Subtitled-Carla-Juri/dp/B00PGV6QN8).
 
## 29. Parthenope (2024)
 
 In Paolo Sorrentino’s ‘Parthenope,’ we meet a young woman named Parthenope, who is from Naples, Italy. The visually stunning movie follows her as she explores her sexuality with men of all ages, and Sorrentino showcases this in a psychedelic fashion, one that fits the beauty of the young woman. However, on a deeper level, the movie is a powerful commentary on the strength of female existence and desire, approached with a sense of unorthodox wonder whose naked vanity is well-deserved. It can be streamed [here](https://www.hbomax.com/movies/parthenope/3ccfe5d6-fe90-4441-a324-ab90a68c49cd).
 
## 28. The Concubine (2012)
 
 This South Korean drama went viral at the time of its release because of all the boldness and nudity, which, although it was purported, wasn’t expected much. In a literal context, a concubine would mean a woman who lives as a mistress with a man of a higher social status (possibly a king of older times) along with his wives and extended family. ‘The Concubine’ encompasses a similar concept wherein, in the Joseon Dynasty, an incumbent prince, Sung-won, falls for the daughter of a nobleman, Hwa-Yeon, who, in turn, is in love with a low-born man, Kwon-Yoo. With sex scenes comprising full and frontal nudity most of the time, ‘The Concubine’ is often counted as one of the most erotic and sensational South Korean movies of all time. Not porn at the outset, but extremely sensual and sexy at that. You can watch it [here](https://tubitv.com/movies/652742/the-concubine-subbed).

## 27. Basic Instinct (1992)
 
 Catherine Tramell is one of the deadliest characters in history. Period! She is also one of the female characters who heated up the nerves with her sultriness and naked adventures. ‘Basic Instinct’ is one of those movies that could give you the fever, and there is no better movie in this list that flamboyantly fondles nudity as it does. The 6-minute-long and raunchy scene between Nick and Catherine is also a major depository of this explicit tale. And who could forget the most paused moment in the history of movies with Sharon Stone baring it all? Or at least deliberately trying to? You can watch the film [here](https://www.paramountplus.com/movies/video/nmiaKYc_zX3YdU1YlslqqmI_zboLhUAe/).
 
## 26. Spun (2002)
 
 A fair warning – do not judge the movie’s content from the picture shown above. How crazy could one become after a drug binge? ‘Spun’ has the answer. Its storyline goes like this – a meth addict gets high and visits a strip club, takes a dancer home with whom he already has a relationship with. His hallucinations turn perverse with sexual fantasies as he tries different sex positions with the girl he picked while he ties her naked on the bed and pulls off a complete ’50 Shades of Grey’ on her. As erotic and intriguing the storyline might seem to you, the more disturbing it actually becomes. You can watch ‘Spun’ [here](https://tubitv.com/movies/454495/spun).
 
## 25. Lust, Caution (2007)
 
 ‘Lust, Caution’ has often been called Ang Lee’s masterpiece. A spy thriller at the outset, the movie is set around the assassination attempts of a few top Japanese officials by Chinese adversaries back when Shanghai and Hong Kong were ruled by namesake Governments run by the Imperial Japanese Army. The attempts of these so-called honey traps would comprise sultry women and steamy sex, hence perhaps the presence of the word “Lust” in the movie’s title. More than plain, simple sex, the eroticism is sweepingly good, and it would be difficult not to be aroused and amused at the same time while watching the movie. You can watch the film [here](https://www.vudu.com/content/browse/details/Lust-Caution-R-Rated-/130432).
 
## 24. Caligula (1979)
 
 Fun fact – ‘Caligula’ is based on the life of a Roman Emperor of the same name. Produced by a leading Men’s magazine, it is no wonder they haven’t left a lot to our imagination.
